fields.Title: KINEEMA / SERIAL NUMBER
fields.Description:
1. Ask Alice to run the serial number you got from the boot.
2. Come back the next day to get results and ask for Alice to try to get more personal info on the mercenary (finish task to run serial number, gain task to get personal info from serial number).
3. Come back the next day to get personal info (finish task to get personal info from serial number).

fields.Title: Alice: ""No problem, officer. Just glad we..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "No problem, officer. Just glad we got it straightened out. I'll contact the ICP database immediately. Call back tomorrow. Hopefully they'll have dug up something useful to your investigation by then."

fields.Title: Alice: ""Officer, as much as I appreciate y..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Officer, as much as I appreciate your efforts to lighten the mood, we both have important work to get back to. Did you have any other *serious* questions?"
fields.Alternate1: "Officer, I suspect you're just trying to keep me on the line, and I just... don't have time for this. Do you have any other *serious* questions?"

fields.Title: You: ""This doesn't seem relevant to my i..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "This doesn't seem relevant to my investigation." (Conclude the conversation.)

fields.Title: Visual Calculus: "A suit of armour like this would ha..."
fields.Dialogue Text: A suit of armour like this would have been manufactured with a particular person's physique in mind. You should ask for whom this suit was fitted.

fields.Title: Alice: ""Sure. Call back tomorrow. Hopefull..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Sure. Call back tomorrow. Hopefully I will have more information for you then."

fields.Title: Esprit de Corps: "This is a fun challenge for her, an..."
fields.Dialogue Text: This is a fun challenge for her, an opportunity to contribute beyond doing her job by rote. She'll gladly put in the extra effort for team RCM!

fields.Title: You: ""Lelystad is probably where he got..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Lelystad is probably where he got the name *Lely*."
fields.Alternate1: "Lelystad is probably where he got the name Lely."

dialogueEntries.conditionsString: Variable["tc.scab_leader_kortenaer"] == false  and  Variable["tc.scab_leader_is_a_merc"] == false  and  Variable["tc.name_kortenaer"] == false  and  Variable["TASK.talk_merc_tattoo_done"] == false  and  Variable["whirling.klaasje_katarzine_lelystad"] == false  and  Variable["plaza.kineema_serial_logic_lely"]

fields.Title: Encyclopedia: "I don't know about you, but I reall..."
fields.Dialogue Text: I don't know about you, but I really, really enjoyed it. Worked out really well in the end.

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: "The lieutenant leans in to listen,..."
fields.Dialogue Text: The lieutenant leans in to listen, notebook in hand.

fields.Title: You: ""So all we have to connect him to K..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "So all we have to connect him to Krenel is the armour."

fields.Title: You: ""Well, we have his name and service..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Well, we have his name and service record now." (Move on.)

fields.Title: Alice: ""The most recently registered firm..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "The most recently registered firm that the ICP has been able to connect to the CdP is a military contractor called *Krenel*. And the one before it was Downwell. I think they might be the same contractor."

fields.Title: Alice: ""He was found as a newborn, in a le..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "He was found as a newborn, in a leaf compactor, near an abandoned farm. He spent four months in the neonatal unit -- survived, apparently -- and was assigned to a foster family at two."

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: "The lieutenant nods -- then jots it..."
fields.Dialogue Text: The lieutenant nods -- then jots it down in his notes: "Lelystad -- Lely. I like that."

fields.Title: Alice: ""They couldn't find anything on the..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "They couldn't find anything on the full code you gave me. However, the first eight characters were match for a series of paintings by Tobias Pren -- you know, that artist who recently hanged himself?"

fields.Title: Alice: ""Does that seem relevant to your in..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Does that seem relevant to your investigation?"

fields.Title: You: ""No, what were his paintings like?""
fields.Dialogue Text: "No, what were his paintings like?"

fields.Title: Alice: ""Celebrity problems.""
fields.Dialogue Text: "Celebrity problems."

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: ""Armour like this isn't mass-produc..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Armour like this isn't mass-produced -- it would have probably been fitted. Perhaps there's a record of who signed for this particular suit of armour."

fields.Title: Inland Empire: "This means something to him. To kno..."
fields.Dialogue Text: This means something to him. To know that name. Like naming a case. It's important.

fields.Title: You: ""Cool... and what's the Moralintern?""
fields.Dialogue Text: "Cool... and what's the Moralintern?"

fields.Title: Electrochemistry: "She means pills and alcohol. See, p..."
fields.Dialogue Text: She means pills and alcohol. See, pills and alcohol make you *a celebrity*. Hasn't it been a while since you've had any?

fields.Title: You: ""Do you know what it's called now?""
fields.Dialogue Text: "Do you know what it's called now?"

fields.Title: Alice: ""Sorry, sir. I still haven't heard..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Sorry, sir. I still haven't heard back from the database people. Try calling again later. Is there anything else I can do for you?"

fields.Title: Authority: "There's a slightly weary, condescen..."
fields.Dialogue Text: There's a slightly weary, condescending note in her voice. She doesn't trust your professionalism following your rather tasteless come-ons.

fields.Title: Alice: ""Yes. The armour was produced by......"
fields.Dialogue Text: "Yes. The armour was produced by..." She looks at her notes. "Fairweather in their facilities in Betancourt, Sur-la-Clef, in '42."

fields.Title: You: ""Art is extremely relevant to my in..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Art is extremely relevant to my investigation. Thank you." (Conclude the conversation.)

fields.Title: Alice: ""That suit of armour was issued to..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "That suit of armour was issued to an Oranjese citizen named Ellis Kortenaer -- that's E-L-L-I-S K-O-R-T-E-N-A-E-R. Exact date of birth unknown. He was signed into the Lelystad County Neonatal Care Unit on 28th of February, 09."

fields.Title: You: ""The world will end soon.""
fields.Dialogue Text: "The world will end soon."

fields.Title: Alice: ""Got it. I'll contact the ICP datab..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Got it. I'll contact the ICP database immediately. Call back tomorrow. Hopefully they'll have dug up something useful by then."

fields.Title: Alice: ""Yes, but the ICP tends to be reluc..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Yes, but the ICP tends to be reluctant to share private sector records. I could try to talk them into it, though."

fields.Title: Alice: ""No problem, lieutenant." She sound..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "No problem, lieutenant." She sounds pleased.

fields.Title: You: ""I'm not sure how this relates to m..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "I'm not sure how this relates to my investigation yet, but I'm sure it does." (Conclude the conversation.)

fields.Title: Alice: ""I hope so. Anything else I can do..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "I hope so. Anything else I can do for you?"

fields.Title: Alice: ""This is what the ICP knows about h..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "This is what the ICP knows about him: He was raised by foster parents, entered the Ijsbrand Military Academy -- in Vredefort -- at 17, then served in the Oranjese forces till he was honourably discharged in '41, just a year before the Semenese conflict."

fields.Title: Authority: "A compliment from Lieutenant Kitsur..."
fields.Dialogue Text: A compliment from Lieutenant Kitsuragi! Not bad.

fields.Title: Alice: ""I'm glad the inquiry was helpful t..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "I'm glad the inquiry was helpful to your investigation, officer. Did you have any other questions?"

fields.Title: Alice: ""Sure, officer. What's the number?..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Sure, officer. What's the number? And the make of the armour, if you know it?"

fields.Title: You: ""No, but thank you for looking into..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "No, but thank you for looking into it."

fields.Title: Alice: ""Just doing my job, officer. Was th..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Just doing my job, officer. Was there anything else?"

fields.Title: Alice: ""Yes!" She seems glad you guessed i..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Yes!" She seems glad you guessed it. "That is the most recent name the ICP has been able to connect to the CdP. And the one before it was Downwell. I also have one called Sediment -- but I think that might be a different contractor..."

fields.Title: You: ""Yes, please do try. It's imperativ..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Yes, please do try. It's imperative that we learn whose armour this was."

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: ""It is! Thank you, Alice!""
fields.Dialogue Text: "It is! Thank you, Alice!"

fields.Title: Alice: ""It was part of a special order for..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "It was part of a special order for Corps de Pharmacie, a security firm contracted to protect the interests of Oranjese pharmaceutical companies. In the Semenine conflict."

fields.Title: You: ""Yes, absolutely! This is exactly w..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Yes, absolutely! This is exactly what I wanted."

fields.Title: You: ""Yes, thank you, officer. I really..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Yes, thank you, officer. I really appreciate your efforts in this case."

fields.Title: You: ""You are my beautiful conquering he..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "You are my beautiful conquering heroine."

fields.Title: You: ""You're right. I meant to say E50.1..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "You're right. I meant to say E50.100.1000. Sorry for the confusion."

fields.Title: You: ""No, why did he hang himself?""
fields.Dialogue Text: "No, why did he hang himself?"

fields.Title: You: ""I'm guessing one of its names is K..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "I'm guessing one of its names is Krenel."

fields.Title: You: ""First, has the firm continued to w..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "First, has the firm continued to work for pharmaceutical companies through all these name changes?"

fields.Title: Alice: "You hear her fingers on a keyboard...."
fields.Dialogue Text: You hear her fingers on a keyboard. "No, they were called *Sediment*. And *Somatosensor*, it seems. All that during the last nine years."

fields.Title: You: ""E50.100.1000. The make and model o..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "E50.100.1000. The make and model of the armour is Fairweather T-500 / VE."

fields.Title: Alice: ""They couldn't find anything on the..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "They couldn't find anything on the full code you gave me. However, the first ten characters tracked to a custom-made baby stroller made in Vaasa City ten years ago."

fields.Title: Alice: ""I'm glad the inquiry was helpful t..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "I'm glad the inquiry was helpful to your investigation, officer. Did you have any other questions?"

fields.Title: Alice: ""Even that took quite a bit of conv..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Even that took quite a bit of convincing to retrieve the information from the database, officer."

fields.Title: You: ""Any information on his foster pare..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Any information on his foster parents?"

fields.Title: You: ""Wait, what's ICP?""
fields.Dialogue Text: "Wait, what's ICP?"

fields.Title: Alice: ""Okay." She's not worried. "Does th..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Okay." She's not worried. "Does that mean you're ready?"

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: ""Hah! Yes -- what Klaasje said. Ver..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Hah! Yes -- what Klaasje said. Very good. That makes sense to me." He takes a quick note.

fields.Title: Alice: ""No, and I doubt they'll get back t..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "No, and I doubt they'll get back to me before tomorrow morning. Anything else?"

fields.Title: Alice: ""Are you sure that's the right numb..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Are you sure that's the right number? Doesn't sound like a serial."

fields.Title: Alice: ""Well, I'll contact the ICP databas..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Well, I'll contact the ICP database immediately. Call back tomorrow. Hopefully they'll have dug up something useful to your investigation by then."

fields.Title: Alice: ""Yes. It took some convincing, but..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Yes. It took some convincing, but I got the mercenary's name and a few biographical details. Are you ready?"
fields.Alternate1: "Yes. I got the mercenary's name and a few biographical details. Are you ready?"

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: ""A name -- this is very good. Ellis..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "A name -- this is very good. Ellis Kortenaer..." he says to himself.

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: ""Even that is a small miracle -- th..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Even that is a small miracle -- these *organizations* usually double check their inventory." He leans closer and shouts: "Thank you, Alice. Great work!"

fields.Title: Empathy: "There's just a hint of weariness in..."
fields.Dialogue Text: There's just a hint of weariness in her voice. It's not that she doesn't trust you -- she just wants to be thorough so as not to create extra work for both of you.

fields.Title: Alice: ""Very pretty pictures of assorted w..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Very pretty pictures of assorted wildlife meant to inspire viewers and look good over couches in office building lobbies." She hesitates. "I've always sort of thought they were trash."

fields.Title: Alice: ""Great. Anything else I can do for..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Great. Anything else I can do for you?"

fields.Title: You: ""Okay.""
fields.Dialogue Text: "Okay."

fields.Title: You: ""Neonatal Care Unit?""
fields.Dialogue Text: "Neonatal Care Unit?"

fields.Title: You: ""X54156745678222. The make and mode..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "X54156745678222. The make and model of the armour is Fairweather T-500 / VE."

fields.Title: Encyclopedia: "The International Collaboration Pol..."
fields.Dialogue Text: The International Collaboration Police (ICP) is an interisolary law enforcement service, the crown jewel in the Moralintern diadem alongside EPIS and the Coalition Government.

fields.Title: You: ""I was born ready, baby!""
fields.Dialogue Text: "I was born ready, baby!"

fields.Title: Inland Empire: "According to Klaasje, Lely said his..."
fields.Dialogue Text: According to Klaasje, Lely said his real name wasn't really *his* -- perhaps that's because he was fostered?

fields.Title: Alice: ""Was there anything else?""
fields.Dialogue Text: "Was there anything else?"

fields.Title: Alice: ""Then the armour followed him to Se..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Then the armour followed him to Semenine -- or at least I assume it did. And that's it. There are no records of his employment in Krenel. Or any of its other incarnations. Or him even entering Revachol.

fields.Title: You: ""AO5577789RHG9999. The make and mod..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "AO5577789RHG9999. The make and model of the armour is Fairweather T-500 / VE."

fields.Title: Alice: "She browses pages. "So... it seems..."
fields.Dialogue Text: She browses pages. "So... it seems the armour went to Semenine. That's where the paper trail ends, though. Even the firm has proven difficult to track. Corps de Pharmacie has been renamed several times over in the years since the armour was issued."

fields.Title: Alice: ""Hard to say. Their client list is..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Hard to say. Their client list is rather diverse. And... incomplete. The only constant seems to be that the mercenaries are always deployed in third- and fourth-world countries."

fields.Title: Alice: ""Glad to help. Call back tomorrow...."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Glad to help. Call back tomorrow. Hopefully I'll have more for you then."

fields.Title: Alice: ""I... don't know what that means. B..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "I... don't know what that means. But -- sure."

fields.Title: Alice: ""Still no word I'm afraid, sir. I k..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Still no word I'm afraid, sir. I know it must be frustrating. Was there anything else you wanted to ask?"

fields.Title: Alice: ""Not yet -- but I was able to convi..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Not yet -- but I was able to convince the database people to share private sector information. They promised to get back to me by tomorrow morning. Did you have any other questions?"

fields.Title: You: ""That's definitely the right number.""
fields.Dialogue Text: "That's definitely the right number."

fields.Title: You: ""Is there any way to find out who g..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Is there any way to find out who got this particular suit of armour?"
fields.Alternate1: "A suit of armour like this would have been customized to fit the wearer. There must be a record of the person to whom it was issued."

fields.Title: Logic: "Joyce said the dead man went by Lel..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Joyce said the dead man went by Lely. He must have gotten that from *Lelystad* -- the name of the county.

fields.Title: Alice: ""I'm going to ignore that, officer...."
fields.Dialogue Text: "I'm going to ignore that, officer. Call back tomorrow. Hopefully I will have more information for you then."

fields.Title: You: ""Shoot.""
fields.Dialogue Text: "Shoot."

fields.Title: Drama: "I knew this would lead to something..."
fields.Dialogue Text: I knew this would lead to something good!

fields.Title: Alice: ""None, officer. Sorry.""
fields.Dialogue Text: "None, officer. Sorry."

fields.Title: Alice: ""If you say so, officer -- of cours..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "If you say so, officer -- of course."

fields.Title: Esprit de Corps: "Sometimes police work is about huma..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Sometimes police work is about human dignity -- about giving back names to anonymous victims.

fields.Title: Alice: ""The International Collaboration Po..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "The International Collaboration Police? Uhm..." She seems confused for a second. "They keep detailed records of all military technology produced by licensed manufacturers. That's one of the reasons the Moralintern spearheaded the creation of the ICP in the first place."

fields.Title: Alice: ""Great. Anything else I could do fo..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Great. Anything else I could do for you?"

fields.Title: Drama: "We're still glad you did it, my lie..."
fields.Dialogue Text: We're still glad you did it, my liege. This was good training. For when you need to lie to save your life maybe?

fields.Title: You: ""Wait, he was found in a... leaf co..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Wait, he was found in a... leaf compactor?"

fields.Title: Alice: ""It's a garden tool used to press l..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "It's a garden tool used to press leaves into these... cubes. It's a detail the hospital had -- the only detail in these files. So I thought it would be good for you to know."

fields.Title: Alice: ""It's all I could learn, I'm afraid..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "It's all I could learn, I'm afraid. That's the serial number you gave me. Anything else I can do for you?"

fields.Title: You: ""So his name wasn't *his* because h..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "So his name wasn't *his* because he was fostered?"
